// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// DEAL View Grammar — dealview.ebnf
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// Language:  DEAL — Digital Engineering Authoring Language
// Version:   0.1.0-draft
// Notation:  W3C EBNF (XML 1.0 Fifth Edition §6)
// Status:    Drafted via grammar-architect workflow (view-grammar extension)
//
// This file defines the grammar for .dealview view-sidecar files — the
// third extension-selected grammar mode (GV-9). A view is membership +
// layout (GV-13): what a diagram shows and where/how it draws it. View
// state is never model; the canonical model lives in .deal/.dealx text.
//
// It depends on lexical.ebnf for all token definitions (including the
// mode-scoped Section 9 view tokens: VIEW_IDENT, HEX_COLOR, DOUBLE_STAR)
// and imports shared productions from deal.ebnf (HeaderBlock, Expression).
//
// Design decisions implemented:
//   GV-2   CSS-shaped sidecar, attribute-selector keys, qualified-path keying
//   GV-3   auto-layout base layer — sidecar stores deltas only
//   GV-9   .dealview as extension-selected mode; theme file + file-per-view
//   GV-13  membership via include/exclude; no-fabrication invariant
//   FS-2   shared @header block
//
// Grammar-lock decisions (registered here; see Decision Record, Section 8):
//   DV-1   .dealview lexer mode: hyphenated VIEW_IDENT + HEX_COLOR +
//          DOUBLE_STAR; whitespace-required binary minus in filter exprs
//   DV-2   edge selector is the string form [deal-connect="from -> to"],
//          with a defined micro-grammar inside the string
//   DV-3   declarations are an OPEN name:value shape; the property
//          vocabulary is a normative table validated by `deal check --views`
//   DV-4   built-in theme-slot vocabulary locked as: base, accent, muted
//
// Shared productions imported from deal.ebnf:
//   HeaderBlock, Expression
//
// Dependency direction is one-way (GV-9): .deal/.dealx never reference
// .dealview constructs; deleting any .dealview never affects `deal build`.
//
// NO-FABRICATION INVARIANT (GV-13, ADR verification item 11):
// This grammar contains NO element-declaring production. Every production
// below either references model elements (selectors, membership patterns)
// or declares presentation state (declarations, tokens). Showing something
// the model does not contain is unrepresentable, not merely checked.
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 1: File Structure
// Design decisions: GV-9, FS-2
// Layer: L5 (View)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * Top-level production for a .dealview file.
 * Same @header preamble as .deal/.dealx (FS-2; schema field is
 * "dealview/0.1"), then any sequence of view content. There is NO
 * package declaration and NO import declaration — a view is not a
 * model namespace and participates in no namespace graph (GV-9:
 * views are bound by co-location or deal.toml [views] registration,
 * never by import).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, FS-2
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "@" (header), "view" | "tokens" | "include" | "exclude"
 *   | "[" | VIEW_IDENT (if no header)
 * Normalization: DealviewFile root AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L1     — theme file: header, tokens, type rules
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L1    — co-located view: header, view block,
 *                                  include, instance rules, edge rules
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   "@" uniquely starts the header (only annotation form in this mode).
 *   All content forms are then distinguished by one token — see
 *   _DealviewContent.
 */
DealviewFile ::=
    HeaderBlock?
    _DealviewContent*
    EOF

/**
 * View file content — the five content forms, in any order and number.
 *
 * Grammar permits any combination so that theme files (tokens + type
 * rules, no view/include) and per-view files (view + include + instance
 * rules) share one shape. Sema constraints (not grammar):
 *   - at most one `view {}` block per file
 *   - at most one `tokens {}` block per file
 *   - theme files (deal.toml [views].theme) should not contain
 *     instance selectors (W-code, non-blocking)
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens per alternative:
 *   "view"     → ViewBlock
 *   "tokens"   → TokensBlock
 *   "include"  → IncludeBlock
 *   "exclude"  → ExcludeBlock
 *   "[", other VIEW_IDENT → Rule
 * Normalization: transparent
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   LL(1). The four block names are CONTEXTUAL keywords at this
 *   position only (DV-1 / lexical.ebnf Section 9): no element kind is
 *   named view/tokens/include/exclude, so a type-selector Rule can
 *   never legitimately begin with these spellings at file level.
 */
_DealviewContent ::=
    ViewBlock
    | TokensBlock
    | IncludeBlock
    | ExcludeBlock
    | Rule


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 2: View Block
// Design decisions: GV-9, GV-13, DV-3
// Layer: L5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * View properties block — diagram-level configuration.
 * Reuses the open declaration shape (DV-3); the view-level property
 * vocabulary is part of the normative table (Section 7): title,
 * viewpoint, direction, layout, grid, edge-labels, dangling-edges.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, GV-13 (dangling-edges), DV-3
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "view"
 * Normalization: ViewBlock AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L23-28 —
 *     view { title: "EV Platform — System Structure";
 *            viewpoint: structure; grid: 20; direction: left-to-right; }
 *   model/views/icd.dealview:L24-30 —
 *     edge-labels: via carrying; dangling-edges: hide;
 */
ViewBlock ::=
    "view" DeclarationBlock


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 3: Tokens Block
// Design decisions: GV-9 (token resolution chain), DV-4
// Layer: L5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * Workspace token definitions — the middle layer of the three-layer
 * resolution chain (GV-9 deferred detail, locked here):
 *
 *   rule value (`stroke: power`)
 *     → workspace token (this block)
 *       → built-in slot (base | accent | muted — DV-4), resolved
 *         against the active editor theme, OR
 *       → color literal with light()/dark() variants, resolved
 *         against the active color mode.
 *
 * Lives in the workspace theme file (deal.toml [views].theme) by
 * convention; grammar does not forbid it in per-view files (sema W-code
 * advises against it).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, DV-4
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "tokens"
 * Normalization: TokensBlock AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L41-52 — aliases (surface: base) and
 *   mode-variant literals (power: light(#B45309) dark(#F59E0B))
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   Separator discipline matches DeclarationBlock: ";" between
 *   declarations, optional before "}".
 */
TokensBlock ::=
    "tokens" "{"
        ( TokenDeclaration ( ";" TokenDeclaration )* ";"? )?
    "}"

/**
 * Single workspace-token definition: name, then either a built-in
 * slot alias or one-or-two color-mode variants.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, DV-4
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: VIEW_IDENT
 * Normalization: TokenDeclaration AST node
 *
 * Sema (not grammar): each of light()/dark() at most once per token;
 * a single-variant token is legal and the renderer derives the other
 * mode (W-code recommends declaring both).
 */
TokenDeclaration ::=
    VIEW_IDENT ":" TokenValue

/**
 * Token value — built-in slot alias or mode-variant color literal(s).
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-4 (slot list locked: base, accent, muted)
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens per alternative:
 *   "base" | "accent" | "muted" → _BuiltinSlot
 *   "light" | "dark"            → _ColorVariant+
 * Normalization: transparent
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   LL(1) — the five spellings are disjoint. All five are contextual
 *   (ordinary VIEW_IDENTs outside this position). A token may NOT
 *   alias another workspace token (single-level resolution — keeps
 *   the chain acyclic by construction).
 */
TokenValue ::=
    _BuiltinSlot
    | _ColorVariant+

/**
 * Built-in theme slots — the normative vocabulary every renderer
 * provides, resolved against the active editor theme.
 *
 * LOCKED (DV-4): exactly these three. Growth is additive via a future
 * grammar revision; renderers must support all listed slots.
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-4
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L43-44 — surface: base; emphasis: accent;
 */
_BuiltinSlot ::=
    "base" | "accent" | "muted"

/**
 * Color-mode variant — light(...) or dark(...) wrapping a hex literal.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-9, DV-1 (HEX_COLOR token)
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "light", "dark"
 * Normalization: ColorVariant AST node (mode, color)
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L47 — light(#B45309) dark(#F59E0B)
 */
_ColorVariant ::=
    ( "light" | "dark" ) "(" HEX_COLOR ")"


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 4: Membership (include / exclude)
// Design decisions: GV-13
// Layer: L5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * Include block — declares what the view shows. A co-located view
 * with no include block shows everything in its served file (GV-13
 * default; backward compatible with sidecar-only layout files).
 *
 * SysML v2 mapping (GV-13): include patterns lower to expose
 * (MembershipExpose / NamespaceExpose); `filter` lowers to
 * ElementFilterMember (Clause 8.2.2.26).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "include"
 * Normalization: IncludeBlock AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/views/thermal.dealview:L40-44 — subtree glob + member sets
 *   model/traceability.dealview:L34-39 — kind filters + exact paths
 */
IncludeBlock ::=
    "include" _MembershipBlock

/**
 * Exclude block — trims elements matched by include. Applied after
 * include resolution; an element is visible iff matched by include
 * (or the co-location default) and not matched by exclude.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "exclude"
 * Normalization: ExcludeBlock AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/views/thermal.dealview:L46-49 —
 *     exclude { model.EVPlatform.Thermal.reservoir; }
 */
ExcludeBlock ::=
    "exclude" _MembershipBlock

/**
 * Membership block body — semicolon-separated pattern list.
 * ";" between patterns, optional before "}".
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "{"
 * Normalization: transparent — list of MembershipPattern nodes
 */
_MembershipBlock ::=
    "{" ( MembershipPattern ( ";" MembershipPattern )* ";"? )? "}"

/**
 * Membership pattern — the three pattern families of GV-13.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens per alternative:
 *   "kind"             → KindFilter
 *   "filter"           → PredicateFilter
 *   other VIEW_IDENT   → PathPattern
 * Normalization: MembershipPattern AST node
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   LL(1). "kind" and "filter" are contextual at pattern-start only;
 *   a model element named kind/filter can still appear MID-path
 *   (e.g. model.kind.x) since only the first token is tested, and at
 *   pattern start an element literally named `kind` is reachable via
 *   its qualified parent path. Validation: every pattern must resolve
 *   against the IR (`deal check --views`, ADR verification item 10).
 */
MembershipPattern ::=
    KindFilter
    | PredicateFilter
    | PathPattern

/**
 * Kind filter — all elements of a metaclass, optionally scoped.
 * `kind(requirement) within requirements.system;`
 *
 * The kind name is an OPEN VIEW_IDENT (DV-3 discipline): the normative
 * kind vocabulary is the IR element-kind set (part_def, port_def,
 * connection_def, flow_def, item_def, attribute_def, action_def,
 * state_def, need, requirement, constraint_def, use_case, interface_def,
 * allocation_def, system, subsystem, component, connect, allocate,
 * satisfy, validate, expose) — validated by sema against the IR schema,
 * not enumerated in the grammar, so IR growth never bumps the grammar.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "kind"
 * Normalization: KindFilter AST node (kind, scope?)
 *
 * SysML v2 mapping: expose + ElementFilterMember on metaclass.
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/views/bdd.dealview:L33 — kind(part_def) within vehicle;
 *   model/views/icd.dealview:L40-42 — three kind filters with scopes
 */
KindFilter ::=
    "kind" "(" VIEW_IDENT ")" ( "within" PathPattern )?

/**
 * Predicate filter — arbitrary boolean expression over element
 * properties. Reuses the deal.ebnf expression grammar.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "filter"
 * Normalization: PredicateFilter AST node
 *
 * Lexical note (DV-1): inside the expression, binary minus requires
 * surrounding whitespace; "a-b" is one VIEW_IDENT.
 *
 * Showcase example: none yet (ADR GV-13 names the form; the showcase
 * exercises globs, sets, and kind filters — a filter example should be
 * added to the corpus when the first predicate use case lands).
 *
 * SysML v2 mapping: ElementFilterMember (Clause 8.2.2.26).
 */
PredicateFilter ::=
    "filter" Expression

/**
 * Path pattern — qualified path with optional wildcards and a
 * terminal-position subtree glob or member set.
 *
 * Pattern forms (GV-13):
 *   model.EVPlatform.Thermal             exact qualified path
 *   model.EVPlatform.*                   one-level wildcard (any step)
 *   model.EVPlatform.Thermal.**          subtree glob (terminal only)
 *   model.EVPlatform.X.{coolantIn, coolantOut}   member set (terminal only)
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: VIEW_IDENT, "*"
 * Normalization: PathPattern AST node (steps[], terminal?)
 *
 * Ambiguity notes:
 *   After ".", one token decides: VIEW_IDENT | "*" continues the head;
 *   DOUBLE_STAR or "{" is the terminal. "**" and "{...}" are
 *   GRAMMATICALLY terminal — mid-path subtree globs and member sets
 *   are unrepresentable.
 *   Path steps must be hyphen-free (model identifiers are IDENT);
 *   a hyphenated VIEW_IDENT step is a sema error (cannot resolve).
 */
PathPattern ::=
    _PathStep ( "." _PathStep )* ( "." _PathTerminal )?

/**
 * Path step — a name or one-level wildcard.
 *
 * Layer: L5 | Marker: [ext]
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 */
_PathStep ::=
    VIEW_IDENT
    | "*"

/**
 * Terminal path element — subtree glob or member set.
 *
 * Layer: L5 | Marker: [ext]
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * FIRST tokens per alternative: DOUBLE_STAR → glob; "{" → MemberSet
 */
_PathTerminal ::=
    DOUBLE_STAR
    | MemberSet

/**
 * Member set — explicit sibling selection at one path position.
 * `model.EVPlatform.EnergyStorage.{coolantIn, coolantOut}`
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-13
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "{"
 * Normalization: MemberSet AST node
 *
 * Ambiguity notes: "{" after "." is unambiguous — DeclarationBlock
 * braces never follow a dot.
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/views/thermal.dealview:L42 — .{coolantIn, coolantOut};
 */
MemberSet ::=
    "{" VIEW_IDENT ( "," VIEW_IDENT )* "}"


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 5: Rules and Selectors
// Design decisions: GV-2, GV-3, DV-2
// Layer: L5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * Rule — a selector and its declaration block. The cascade (GV-2/GV-3):
 *
 *   auto-layout  <  theme type rules  <  per-view type rules
 *               <  attribute-refined type rules  <  instance rules
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2, GV-3
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: VIEW_IDENT (type rule), "[" (instance/edge rule)
 * Normalization: Rule AST node (selector, declarations)
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L56-64   — system { fill: surface; ... }
 *   model/global.dealview:L101-104 — connect[carrying="PowerDelivery"] {...}
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L43-45  — [deal-id="model.EVPlatform"] {...}
 */
Rule ::=
    Selector DeclarationBlock

/**
 * Selector — type selector (optionally attribute-refined) or a bare
 * attribute selector (instance / edge rule).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2 (attribute-selector form), DV-2
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens per alternative:
 *   VIEW_IDENT → TypeSelector _AttributeSelector?
 *   "["        → _AttributeSelector (instance/edge rule)
 * Normalization: Selector AST node
 *
 * Ambiguity notes: LL(1) — VIEW_IDENT vs "[" are disjoint.
 */
Selector ::=
    TypeSelector _AttributeSelector?
    | _AttributeSelector

/**
 * Type selector — element-kind default rule (the theme layer).
 *
 * The kind name is an OPEN VIEW_IDENT validated against the same IR
 * element-kind vocabulary as KindFilter (DV-3 discipline). Unknown
 * kinds are sema diagnostics, not syntax errors.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2, GV-9 (theme layer), DV-3
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: VIEW_IDENT
 * Normalization: TypeSelector AST node
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview — system, subsystem, component, port,
 *   connect, need, requirement, allocate, satisfy type rules
 */
TypeSelector ::=
    VIEW_IDENT

/**
 * Attribute selector — [key="value"]. Three roles by key:
 *
 *   [deal-id="<DealIdRef>"]            instance rule (GV-2)
 *   [deal-connect="<DealConnectRef>"]  edge rule (DV-2)
 *   [<other-key>="<string>"]           refinement of a TypeSelector
 *                                      by IR payload property
 *                                      (e.g. connect[carrying="X"])
 *
 * Key discipline (sema, not grammar): deal-id and deal-connect are
 * RESERVED keys, legal only as bare selectors (no preceding
 * TypeSelector); any other key is legal only as a refinement (must
 * follow a TypeSelector and name a property of that kind's IR payload).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2, DV-2
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "["
 * Normalization: AttributeSelector AST node (key, value)
 *
 * Ambiguity notes: "[" begins an attribute selector in every .dealview
 * context where a rule may start. The composition tag token "[<" is
 * never emitted in .dealview mode; no multiplicity exists here.
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/global.dealview:L101 — connect[carrying="PowerDelivery"]
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L111 — [deal-connect="EnergyStorage.hvPowerOut
 *     -> Propulsion.hvPowerIn"]
 */
_AttributeSelector ::=
    "[" VIEW_IDENT "=" STRING_LITERAL "]"

/**
 * Micro-grammar of the deal-id selector string (GV-2): a qualified
 * path. Parsed from the STRING_LITERAL content at parse time so an
 * unparseable reference is a syntax-level diagnostic with a span
 * inside the string; resolution against the IR is sema
 * (`deal check --views`).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2 (qualified path as universal join key, D-23)
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * Normalization: DealIdRef AST node (path steps)
 *
 * Note: segments are plain IDENT (hyphen-free) — these are model
 * identifiers, lexed by the micro-parser in .deal identifier rules.
 */
DealIdRef ::=
    IDENT ( "." IDENT )*

/**
 * Micro-grammar of the deal-connect selector string (DV-2): an
 * endpoint pair selecting a connect by its from/to ports. Endpoints
 * use the same path resolution as connect tags in .dealx (relative
 * to the view's served composition scope).
 *
 * LOCKED (DV-2): the string form is the canonical edge selector,
 * consistent with [deal-id="..."] and CSS attribute-selector shape.
 * (The showcase NOTE flagging this as exemplar syntax is resolved.)
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-2, GV-2
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * Normalization: DealConnectRef AST node (from, to)
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L111 —
 *     [deal-connect="EnergyStorage.hvPowerOut -> Propulsion.hvPowerIn"]
 */
DealConnectRef ::=
    DealIdRef "->" DealIdRef


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 6: Declarations and Values
// Design decisions: GV-2, GV-3, DV-1, DV-3
// Layer: L5
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/**
 * Declaration block — the body of view blocks and rules.
 * ";" separates declarations; optional before "}".
 *
 * SEPARATOR DISCIPLINE (stricter than SD-10's optional-semicolon rule,
 * deliberately): a declaration's value sequence is space-separated and
 * may contain bare identifiers (`edge-labels: via carrying`), so the
 * ";" is what bounds it — without it, the next property name would be
 * consumed as a value. SD-10 relies on a following KEYWORD to
 * disambiguate; .dealview property names are open VIEW_IDENTs (DV-3),
 * so no such keyword exists. The one SD-10-consistent relaxation is
 * the optional trailing ";" before "}".
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-3, GV-2
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "{"
 * Normalization: transparent — list of Declaration nodes
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L43-45 — { x: 40; y: 40; w: 1280; h: 760; }
 */
DeclarationBlock ::=
    "{" ( Declaration ( ";" Declaration )* ";"? )? "}"

/**
 * Declaration — open property: value(s) shape (DV-3).
 *
 * LOCKED (DV-3): any VIEW_IDENT parses as a property name; the
 * normative property vocabulary (Section 7) is validated by
 * `deal check --views` (unknown property → W-code; known property
 * with wrong value type → E-code). CSS-style forward compatibility:
 * renderers gain properties without grammar bumps.
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-3, GV-2, GV-3
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: VIEW_IDENT
 * Normalization: Declaration AST node (name, values[])
 *
 * Ambiguity notes: Value+ is bounded by ";" or "}" — neither token
 * can begin a Value, so the repetition terminates deterministically.
 */
Declaration ::=
    VIEW_IDENT ":" Value+

/**
 * Value — one element of a declaration's value sequence.
 *
 * Design decisions: DV-1, DV-3, GV-9
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens per alternative:
 *   STRING_LITERAL  '"'        → string (title: "...")
 *   "-", [0-9]                 → _SignedNumber (x: 40; stroke-width: 1.5)
 *   BOOLEAN_LITERAL            → boolean (collapsed: true)
 *   HEX_COLOR "#"              → raw color (legal; W-code advises
 *                                workspace tokens instead — GV-9:
 *                                "rules reference workspace tokens
 *                                only" is house style, not grammar)
 *   "("                        → Point (waypoints)
 *   VIEW_IDENT                 → keyword value or token reference
 *                                (fill: surface; routing: orthogonal;
 *                                 direction: left-to-right)
 * Normalization: Value AST node (variant-tagged)
 *
 * Ambiguity notes: all six FIRST sets are disjoint at the token level
 * (BOOLEAN_LITERAL is emitted by the lexer, never VIEW_IDENT).
 */
Value ::=
    STRING_LITERAL
    | _SignedNumber
    | BOOLEAN_LITERAL
    | HEX_COLOR
    | Point
    | VIEW_IDENT

/**
 * Signed number — geometry coordinates may be negative (positions are
 * parent-relative and may extend left/above the local origin).
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-3
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "-", [0-9]
 * Normalization: NumberLiteral AST node
 */
_SignedNumber ::=
    "-"? ( INTEGER_LITERAL | REAL_LITERAL )

/**
 * Point — coordinate pair, used in waypoint sequences.
 *
 * Design decisions: GV-2 (edge-routing waypoints)
 * Layer: L5
 * Marker: [ext]
 * FIRST tokens: "("
 * Normalization: Point AST node (x, y)
 *
 * Showcase example:
 *   model/vehicle.dealview:L112 —
 *     waypoints: (380, 188) (480, 188);
 */
Point ::=
    "(" _SignedNumber "," _SignedNumber ")"


// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Section 7: Normative Property Vocabulary (DV-3)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// The grammar parses any property name (DV-3 open shape). THIS TABLE is
// the normative vocabulary, validated by `deal check --views`:
//   - unknown property name        → W-code (forward-compatible warning)
//   - known name, wrong value type → E-code
// Renderers MUST implement every property below; additions to this table
// are spec revisions but NOT grammar changes.
//
// ── View-level properties (in `view {}`) ──────────────────────────────
//   title            STRING            diagram title
//   viewpoint        ident             structure | definition | interface |
//                                      traceability | behavior | use-case |
//                                      <user-defined>
//   direction        ident             left-to-right | right-to-left |
//                                      top-to-bottom | bottom-to-top
//   layout           ident             layered (default) | tree | grid
//   grid             number            snap-grid pitch (model units)
//   edge-labels      ident+            payload fields shown on edges
//                                      (e.g. via carrying)
//   dangling-edges   ident             stub (default) | hide   (GV-13)
//
// ── Node geometry (instance rules; deltas from auto-layout, GV-3) ─────
//   x, y             number            position, PARENT-RELATIVE
//   w, h             number            size
//   min-w, min-h     number            minimum size (type rules)
//   collapsed        boolean           whole-node collapse
//   <name>-compartment  ident          visible | collapsed | hidden —
//                                      per-compartment state, name from
//                                      the SysML v2 graphical notation
//                                      compartment vocabulary (GV-14),
//                                      e.g. title-compartment,
//                                      attributes-compartment
//
// ── Node style (type or instance rules) ───────────────────────────────
//   fill             token | color     background
//   stroke           token | color     border / line color
//   stroke-width     number            border / line weight
//   corner-radius    number            rounded corners
//   shape            ident             template variant where the
//                                      notation allows one (e.g. port:
//                                      square)
//   size             number            uniform size for symbol nodes
//                                      (ports)
//
// ── Edge style and routing (connect/allocate/satisfy rules) ──────────
//   routing          ident             orthogonal | straight | spline
//   line-style       ident             solid (default) | dashed | dotted
//   arrowhead        ident             open | filled | none
//   waypoints        Point+            route via points (instance rules)
//
// Value type "token | color" means: a VIEW_IDENT naming a workspace
// token (resolved via the tokens {} chain, GV-9) or a raw HEX_COLOR
// (legal; W-code advises tokens for theme coherence).
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Section 8: Decision Record and Verification Summary
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// ── Grammar-lock decisions (to register alongside GV-1..GV-15) ────────
//
// DV-1 — View lexer mode: hyphenated VIEW_IDENT + HEX_COLOR + DOUBLE_STAR
//   .dealview mode extends IDENT with internal hyphens and adds the
//   HEX_COLOR and DOUBLE_STAR tokens (lexical.ebnf Section 9). Binary
//   minus inside filter expressions requires surrounding whitespace.
//   Rejected: parser-composed names (adjacency constraints inexpressible
//   in W3C EBNF); vocabulary rename to snake/camelCase (diverges from
//   the CSS-shaped sidecar GV-2 chose; would churn the corpus).
//
// DV-2 — Edge selector is the string form [deal-connect="from -> to"]
//   Consistent with [deal-id="..."] and the CSS attribute-selector shape
//   (GV-2). The string content has the DealConnectRef micro-grammar,
//   parsed at parse time. Rejected: structured attributes
//   ([deal-connect from=".." to=".."]) — breaks the uniform selector
//   shape for no expressiveness gain.
//
// DV-3 — Open declaration shape + normative property table
//   Declaration ::= VIEW_IDENT ":" Value+ parses any property; Section 7
//   is the normative vocabulary enforced by `deal check --views`.
//   Rejected: closed per-property productions (every renderer addition
//   becomes a grammar bump); hybrid (two rule regimes to maintain).
//   The no-fabrication invariant (GV-13) is unaffected — it concerns
//   element-declaring productions, which this grammar has none of.
//
// DV-4 — Built-in slot vocabulary locked: base, accent, muted
//   Exactly the three slots the ADR names. Growth is additive via spec
//   revision. Rejected: extended semantic-state set (permanent renderer
//   obligations); grammar-agnostic slot list (ADR requires the list to
//   lock with the grammar).
//
// ── Production summary ────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   Public:  DealviewFile, ViewBlock, TokensBlock, TokenDeclaration,
//            TokenValue, IncludeBlock, ExcludeBlock, MembershipPattern,
//            KindFilter, PredicateFilter, PathPattern, MemberSet, Rule,
//            Selector, TypeSelector, DealIdRef, DealConnectRef,
//            DeclarationBlock, Declaration, Value, Point          (21)
//   Helper:  _DealviewContent, _BuiltinSlot, _ColorVariant,
//            _MembershipBlock, _PathStep, _PathTerminal,
//            _AttributeSelector, _SignedNumber                     (8)
//   Imported from deal.ebnf: HeaderBlock, Expression
//   Micro-grammars (inside STRING_LITERAL content): DealIdRef,
//            DealConnectRef
//
// ── LL(1) verification ────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   _DealviewContent:    view/tokens/include/exclude/"["/VIEW_IDENT — disjoint
//   MembershipPattern:   kind/filter/other — disjoint at first token
//   _PathStep vs _PathTerminal (after "."): VIEW_IDENT|"*" vs "**"|"{"
//                        — disjoint (DOUBLE_STAR by longest match)
//   TokenValue:          base|accent|muted vs light|dark — disjoint
//   Selector:            VIEW_IDENT vs "[" — disjoint
//   Value:               '"' / -|digit / bool / "#" / "(" / VIEW_IDENT
//                        — disjoint
//   DeclarationBlock:    Value+ bounded by ";"|"}" (neither starts a Value)
//   → LL(1) at every alternation; no left recursion anywhere.
//
// ── No-fabrication check (GV-13, ADR verification item 11) ────────────
//   Structural: no production in this file introduces a model element.
//   Selectors and membership patterns are references; declarations and
//   tokens are presentation state. Verified by inspection of all 29
//   productions — none contains a definition keyword, a typing operator,
//   or a structural-relationship operator.
//
// ── Showcase coverage (10/10 .dealview files) ─────────────────────────
//   global.dealview         @header, tokens (slots + variants), 9 type rules,
//                           4 attribute-refined rules
//   vehicle.dealview        view block, include (**), 15 instance rules,
//                           2 edge rules with waypoints
//   traceability.dealview   kind() within ×2, exact paths, instance rules
//   views/thermal.dealview  **, member sets ×2, exclude, view props
//   views/icd.dealview      kind() within ×3, edge-labels, dangling-edges,
//                           edge rule
//   views/bdd.dealview      kind() within, exact path, layout: tree
//   views/behaviors.dealview kind() within, exact paths
//   views/use-cases.dealview kind() within, exact path
//   variants/sedan.dealview  **, exact path, compartment property
//   variants/performance.dealview  **, exact path, nested instance rules
//   Not yet exercised by the corpus: PredicateFilter ("filter"), "*"
//   one-level wildcard, "muted" slot, HEX_COLOR with 3/8 digits,
//   negative coordinates. (GA4: corpus additions recommended.)
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// End of dealview.ebnf
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

